      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LUMBER DREAM (2) improved sharply at the latest with a comprehensive win over 1708m at Gawler two-and-a-half weeks ago. No tougher this time and the rise in trip looks to have unlocked him. Can keep the ball rolling now. BADONKIDONK (5) was no match for a dominant winner at Strathalbyn but still did a good job to finish fourth. Has been much better in his last two and boasts a strong record here. Confident he puts in another good performance. WILD WILLY (1) strode forward early from his wide draw last start at Terang only to fade late. Was a good winner in this grade two back at Gawler. No reason he can't recapture that form and be right in the mix. CROWN AND ANCHOR (4) raced on the speed from the outset and went to score over 1800m at Clare. Built nicely into this campaign and has more to offer. GREATESTOFEASE (7) was much better last time at Kingscote when returning to somewhere near his best form. Will get back from the draw and be saved for the final shot at them.",
